UML:TaggedValue.value: Requires that a particular alteration description can be assigned an age using a GeologicEvent entity.
Basic alteration description properties; does not include alteration product to allow decoupling alteration description from EarthMaterial.
requirements based on SWE, but decoupled from SWE to allow other implementations.
Requires that a particular MetamorphicDescription can be assigned an age specified by a GeologicEvent entity.
Requirements class to allow an alteration description to specify alterationProducts as EarthMaterial entity instances.
Basic alteration description properties; does not include alteration product to allow decoupling alteration description from EarthMaterial.
Requires that a particular alteration description can be assigned an age using a GeologicEvent entity.
Requirements class to allow an alteration description to specify alterationProducts as EarthMaterial entity instances.

A ChemicalComposition entity SHALL have exactly one 'chemicalAnalysis' property, specified by a DataRecord entity.
Informative: 'chemicalAnalysis' is an estimated Property
Requires that a particular MetamorphicDescription can be assigned an age specified by a GeologicEvent entity.

A MetamorphicDescription SHALL have one or more protolithLithology property values specified by EarthMaterial entities.
Note: The protolithLithology property is voidable and is an estimated property.

A PlanarOrientationProperties instance is a kind of GeometricDescriptionValue, and SHALL inherit the properties from that class; A PlanarOrientationProperties instance SHALL have a convention property that is a category value specifying the manner in which the orientation value is specified A PlanarOrientationProperties instance MAY have additional properties for azimuth and dip that are numeric range values, and a polarity property that is a code value indicating whether the planar orientation is associated with a directed feature that is overturned, upright, vertical etc. At least one of polarity, azimuth, or dip SHALL have a value that is not nil.

A GeoSciML Quantity Range is a kind of QuantityRange, and SHALL inherit all properties and requirements from QuantityRange, and MAY have a lowerValue property that is a real number, and MAY have an upperValue property that is a real number.

A GeometricDescriptionValue MAY have two properties: determinationMethod: a category that specifies how the orientation value was determined. descriptiveOrientation: a qualitative text specification of the orientation

A QuantitativeAttributeAccuracyProperties instance SHALL have the following properties: One or more 'value' property values that SHALL each be a set of values. The semantics of the values SHALL be determined by an associated 'valueType' template; Exactly one 'valueUnit' property that SHALL provide a name, a MeasureType code value, and an abbreviation for labeling the units (uomSymbol) Informative: Additional properties may be added to the QuantitativeAttributeAccuracy entity by implementations. Recommendation is to use properties defined by ISO 19157 model when applicable.
A quantityRange value SHALL inherit all Properties and requirements from SWE QuantityRange.
A Vector quantity is a kind of LinearOrientation and SHALL inherit all properties from that class, and SHALL have a magnitude property that is specified as a QuantityRange value.

A Term SHALL have a maximum of one preferred name defined for any natural language. A Term SHALL have a URI that uniquely identifies the represented concept and can be used as a token representing the concept in model instances. A Term SHALL have associated metadata documenting the provenance of the represented concept definition.

A GSML element is a kind of GML Feature and SHALL inherit all properties and requirements from that class. A GSML instance SHALL have an association to at least one member that is a GSMLItem A GSML instance MAY have one associated Metadata record that describes the collection.
A GSML collection member SHALL an instance of one of the following classes: EarthMaterial, GeologicFeature, GML geometry object, MappedFeature, GeologicRelation, or SamplingFeature.
A geologic feature relation is a kind of geologic relation for which the source and target classes SHALL BE geologic feature instances.

A GeologicRelation SHALL be categorized by a relationship category term A GeologicRelation instance SHALL have an association to an entity that plays the source role in the relationship A GeologicRelation instance SHALL have associations to one or more entities that play the target role in the relationship. A GeologicRelation may have roles of the source and target entities specified by one source and one target role category terms.

A PhysicalDescription SHALL have a propertyName Property that is a Term entity specifying the kind of property for which the measured value is reported. A PhysicalDescription SHALL have at least one 'propertyMeasure' property that is a Quantity entity instance specifying the measured property value. Informative: The propertyMeasure property is an estimated property.
requirements based on SWE, but decoupled from SWE to allow other implementations.

A Citation SHALL have a 'title' property specified by a CharacterString.
Informative: A Citation MAY have other properties as specified by the ISO19115-1 conceptual model.

An Identifier SHALL have a 'code' property that is specified by a CharacterString.
Informative: An Identifier MAY have a 'codeSpace' property specified by a CharacterString. An Identifier MAY have a 'version' property specified by a CharacterString.

An Identifier SHALL have an 'authority' property specified by a Citation entity.
Informative: The 'authority' property is voidable.

A TimeOrdinalEra SHALL have a 'start' property that is specified by a TimeOrdinalEraBoundary entity. A TimeOrdinalEra SHALL have an 'end' property that is specified by a TimeOrdinalEraBoundary entity. Informative: The 'start' and 'end' properties are voidable.

A TimeOrdinalReferenceSystem instance SHALL have at least two 'referencePoint' properties that are specified by TimeOrdinalEraBoundar instances. If non-nil 'nextEra' or 'previousEra' property instances are associated with a TimeOrdinalReferenceSystem 'referencePoint' TimeOrdinalEraBoundary, then the TimeOrdinalEra that is the target of the 'nextEra' or 'previousEra' property SHALL also be the target of a 'component' property of the TimeOrdinalReferenceSystem.
Informative: the 'referencePoint' property is voidable.
A TimeOrdinalEraBoundary SHALL have exactly one 'position' property specified by a TM_Instant entity as defined by ISO 19107.
A TimeOrdinalReferenceSystem SHALL have at least one 'component' property that is specified by a TimeOrdinalEra entity.

A TimeOrdinalEraBoundary SHALL have exactly one 'positionalUncertainty' property specified by a QuantitativeAttributeAccuracy entity
Informative: The 'positionUncertainty' property on TimeOrdinalEraBoundary is voidable.
A TimeOrdinalEraBoundary SHALL have a 'nextEra' property that is a TimeOrdinalEra; A TimeOrdinalEraBoundary SHALL have a 'previousEra' property that is a TimeOrdinalEra;

An OriginPosition SHALL have a location property that is a geospatial point. An OriginPosition SHALL have an elevation property that is a numeric value specified relative to a datum define w.r.t. the Earth. Informative: The location and elevation properties of OriginPosition are voidable and are estimated. An OriginPosition MAY have one or more relatedBorehole entities that are specified by Borehole instances.
A mappedInterval that fills the role of logElement for a Borehole SHALL have samplingFrame property value that is the borehole for which the interval is a logElement.
A borehole is a kind of sampling curve, and SHALL inherit all properties, associations, and requirements defined for GML v3.1 SF_SamplingCurve.

A DrillingDetails entity SHALL have the following properties: One 'drillingMethod' that is a code value specifying the technology used to make the wellbore; One 'boreholeDiameter' that is a Quantity entity; One 'interval' that is a GML GM_Curve object specifying a geospatial location for the described borehole interval. If 'intervalBegin' and 'intervalEnd' quantities are specified, the value for 'intervalBegin' SHALL be less that the value for 'intervalEnd' Informative: All properties are voidable. The 'boreholeDiameter' is an estimated property. A DrillingDetails instance MAY include one 'intervalBegin' that is a Quantity specifying the coordinate of the beginning of the described interval as a one-dimensional quantity measured along the wellbore trace from the OriginPosition. A DrillingDetails instance MAY include one 'intervalEnd' that is a Quantity specifying the coordinate of the end of the described interval as a one-dimensional quantity measured along the wellbore trace from the OriginPosition.

A borehole SHALL have exactly one linear, 3-D trace (shape) located within the Earth; this trace SHALL be represented by a GML GM_Curve Informative: the Borehole/shape property (inherited from SF_SpatialSamplingFeature) is voidable in GeoSciML v.3.2 if the Borehole instance has an inclinationType (specified by indexData/BoreholeDetails) indicating that the borehole is vertical. NOTE: for interoperability, information exchange profiles may need to restrict the valid subtypes of GM_Curve allowed in instance documents.
An OriginPosition entity is a kind of GML Feature and SHALL inherit the properties and requirements of GML Feature.
A mappedInterval is a kind of MappedFeature and inherits the following properties: observationMethod, specification (mandatory), and positionalAccuracy, resolutionScale (voidable)

A boreholeDetails entity SHALL have the following properties: 'operator' that specifies the person or organization responsible for the borehole 'driller' that specifies the person or organization responsible for drilling the borehole 'dateOfDrilling' that specifies the time period between when drilling started and total depth was reached. 'startPoint' that specifies a code value indicating the position relative to ground surface of the borehole origin. 'inclinationType' that specifies a code value qualitatively indicating the orientation of the borehole relative to the Earth Surface. 'boreholeMaterialCustodian' that specifies the person or organization who is responsible for curating sample materials obtained from the borehole 'purpose' that specifies a code value indicating why the borehole was drilled 'dataCustodian' that specifeis the person or organization who is responsible for curating data obtained from the borehole 'boreholeLength' that specifies a Quantity for the measured length of the well bore. Informative: All properties are voidable. The 'boreholeLength' is an estimated property.
a MappedInterval is a kind of MappedFeature and SHALL inherit all the properties, associations, and requirements of that MappedFeature.

A MappedInterval SHALL have a shape property that is a GM_Curve. If 'mappedIntervalBegin' and 'mappedIntervalEnd' quantities are specified, the value for 'mappedIntervalBegin' SHALL be less that the value for 'mappedIntervalEnd' If 'mappedIntervalBegin' and 'mappedIntervalEnd' quantities are specified, the shape property may have a nil value. Informative: A MappedInterval instance MAY include one 'mappedIntervalBegin' that is a Quantity specifying the coordinate of the beginning of the described interval as a one-dimensional quantity measured along the wellbore trace from the OriginPosition. A MappedInterval instance MAY include one 'mappedIntervalEnd' that is a Quantity specifying the coordinate of the end of the described interval as a one-dimensional quantity measured along the wellbore trace from the OriginPosition. NOTE: specific information interchange profiles should probably constrain the subtypes of GM_Curve that may be used in instance documents in order to facilitate interoperability.
A Borehole is a kind of GML Feature and SHALL inherit all the properties and associations of GML Feature.

RockMaterial is the only concrete subtype of CompoundMaterial, so this requirements class is only provided as an extension point for those wishing to implement extensions with some other kind of CompoundMaterial.

RockMaterial is the only concrete subtype of CompoundMaterial, so this requirements class is only provided as an extension point for those wishing to implement extensions with some other kind of CompoundMaterial.

A CompoundMaterial is a kind of EarthMaterial and SHALL inherit all properties and requirements from EarthMaterial. A CompoundMaterial SHALL have one or more 'compositionCategory' property values specified by a Category entity A CompoundMaterial SHALL have one or more 'geneticCategory' property values specified by a Category entity Informative: The 'compositionCategory' and 'geneticCategory' properties are voidable and are estimated properties.
A MaterialRelation is a GeologicRelation in which the source and target entities SHALL be instances of ConstituentPart

A ParticleGeometryDescription SHALL have the following properties: One 'particleType' that is specified by a term categorizing the kind of particle represented One or more 'aspectRatio' that is specified by a Category entity; One or more 'shape' values that are specified by a Category entity; One 'size' that is specified by a QuantityRange entity One or more 'sorting' values that are specified by a Category entity; One or more 'sourceOrganism' values that are specified by Organism entities. IF 'particleType' is NOT 'fossil' then 'sourceOrganism' must be void. Informative: The 'aspectRatio', 'shape', 'size', 'sorting' properties are voidable and are estimated properties. The 'sourceOrganism' property is voidable.

A CompoundMaterial SHALL have a 'constituent' property that is specified by a ConstituentPart entity A CompoundMaterial SHALL have a 'particleGeometry' property that is specified by a ParticlGeometryDescription entity Informative: The 'constituent' and 'particleGeometry' properties are voidable.

A ConstituentPart instance SHALL have the following properties: One 'role' that is specified by a term value One 'proportion' that is specified by a QuantityRange entity One 'material' that is specified by a concrete subtype of EarthMaterial One 'particleGeometry' that is specified by a ParticleGeometryDescription entity. One or more 'relatedMaterial' that are specified by MaterialRelation instances Informative: The 'proportion' property is an estimated property. The 'material', 'particleGeometry', 'relatedMaterial', and 'proportion' properties are voidable.

An EarthMaterial instance SHALL have a purpose property that is from the set of categories {definingNorm, instance, typicalNorm} An EarthMaterial entity SHALL have a 'geochemistry' property specified by a ChemicalComposition entity An EarthMaterial entity SHALL have at least one 'physicalProperty' property that is specified by a PhysicalDescription entity. An EarthMaterial entity SHALL have at least one color property specified by a Category entity. Informative: The color, geochemistry, and physicalProperty properties are voidable. The color property is an estimated property. EarthMaterial is an abstract class that is instantiated by one of its concrete subtypes: OrganicMaterial, InorganicFluid, Mineral, or RockMaterial.

Informative: An EarthMaterial entity MAY have an associated metadata property that is specified by an entity containing information about the provenance and quality of the entity instance. Recommendation: use the ISO 19115 or ISO19115-1 metadata abstract specification for metadata content.

A RockMaterial is a kind of CompoundMaterial and SHALL inherit all properties and requirements from Compound Material A RockMaterial SHALL have one or more 'lithology' property values that are specified by terms. A RockMaterial SHALL have a 'consolidationDegree' property that is specified by a Category entity Informative: The 'consolidationDegree' property is voidable and is an estimated property.
An instance of 'alterationProperties' SHALL associate a RockMaterial instance to an AlterationDescription instance. Informative: The AlterationDescription MAY have a nil value.
An instance of 'fabric' SHALL associate a RockMaterial instance to an FabricDescription instance. Informative: The FabricDescription MAY have a nil value.
An instance of 'metamorphicProperties' SHALL associate a RockMaterial instance to an MetamorphicDescription instance. Informative: The MetamorphicDescription MAY have a nil value.
A FabricDescription SHALL have a 'fabricType' property value specified by a term that characterized the kind of fabric.

A GeologicEvent is a kind of GeologicFeature and SHALL inherit all the properties and requirements of GeologicFeature. A Geologic event SHALL have at least one of an 'olderNamedAge' and a 'youngerNamedAge' property or a 'numericAgeDate' property. The 'olderNamedAge' and the 'youngerNamedAge' properties SHALL be specified by GeochronologicEra entities. The 'numericAgeDate' property SHALL be specified by a NumericAgeRange entity. A GeologicEvent SHALL have at least one 'eventProcess' property specified by a Term value. A GeologicEvent SHALL have at least one 'eventEnvironment' property specified by a Category entity. A GeologicEvent instance SHALL be the value of either an 'alterationEvent' property or a 'metamorphicEvent' property, but not both. [Target is an instance document...]
Informative: All of the above properties of GeologicEvent are estimated properties and are voidable.

A NumericAgeRange SHALL have a 'reportingDate' property that is specified by a GeologicDateEstimate entity. A NumericAgeRange SHALL have an 'olderBoundDate' property that is specified by a GeologicDateEstimate entity. A NumericAgeRange SHALL have a 'youngerBoundDate' property that is specified by a GeologicDateEstimate entity.
Informative: the 'olderBoundDate' and 'youngerBoundDate' properties are voidable and are estimated properties. The 'reportingDate' property is an estimated property.

A GeologicTimeInstant SHALL have either a 'coordinateValue' property specified by a numeric value, or an 'indeterminatePosition' property specified by an IndeterminantValue string that has a value "unknown". A GeologicTimeInstant SHALL have a 'frame' property specified by a TimeCoordinateSystem entity.
Informative: The TimeCoordinateSystem that is the value of the 'frame' property may simply be specified by supplying the 'code' value for the TimeCoordinateSystem 'identifier' property. TimeCoordinateSystem is a kind of TimeReferenceSystem; it is the only kind of TimeReferenceSystem that is relevant to geologic time instants.

A GeologicDateEstimate SHALL have a 'position' property specified by a GeologicTimeInstant entity A GeologicDateEstimate SHALL have a 'quality' property specified by a QuantitiativeAttributeAccuracy entity.
Informative: The 'position' and 'quality' properties are estimated properties. The 'quality' property is voidable.

A TimeCoordinateSystem SHALL have a 'name' property that is specified by an Identifier. A TimeCoordinateSystem SHALL have an 'origin' property that is specified by a DateTime value. A TimeCoordinateSystem SHALL have an 'interval' property that is specified by a CharacterString value.
Informative A TimeCoordinateSystem MAY have a 'domainOfValidity' property that is specified by one or more Extent entities, each of which is specified by a 'begin' and 'end' property that are GeologicTimeInstant entities referenced to the same TimeCoordinateSystem. The interval should be the name of some well know unit of time duration, e.g. second, year, thousand years, million years.

An Ordinal Age SHALL have an 'olderNamedAge' property that is specified by a GeochronologicEra entity An Ordinal Age SHALL have a 'youngerNamedAge' property that is specified by a GeochronologicEra entity. Informative: It is useful for standardized portrayal of geologic features based on age to assign a 'representativeNamedAge' that is specified by a GeochronologicEra. The 'youngerNamedAge' and 'olderNamedAge' properties are voidable and are estimated properties.
A geologic feature may be associated with a metadata record that provides information about the provenance of the feature

A geologic feature instance represents either a feature instance, a normative feature description that characterizes a feature type, or a typical feature description that characterizes a collection of feature instances.
If the purpose of a geologic feature is 'instance', then it SHALL have at least one Mapped Feature occurrence
A geologic feature instance is the result of one or more observations, and as such has an observation method property that categorizes the method used to characterize the feature properties.
A geologic feature may have one or more associated classifier concepts that categorize the feature.
A geologic feature is a kind of feature and inherits GML abstract feature properties: name, description, bounding box, metadata
A geologic feature may have 1 or more mapped features that represent occurrences of the geologic feature
A mapped feature SHALL have a geospatial location
A mapped feature may be associated with a metadata record that provides information about the provenance of the feature

The resolution of the geospatial location of a mapped feature SHALL BE quantified by a spatial resolution property. The spatial resolution is related to the smallest distance between points on the mapped feature trace that can be distinguished in the database representation of the feature. This is in contrast to position accuracy which is a measure of how well a feature is located relative to other features in the geographic reference system.
A mapped feature MAY be marked as concealed or exposed
A mapped feature is a kind of feature and SHALL inherit the attributes and requirements of abstract GML feature.
A MappedFeature SHALL have a positional accuracy property that specifies the uncertainty in the geospatial positioning of the feature, and the value of the property SHALL be a Quantity value.
A mapped feature SHALL BE associated with exactly one geologic feature that represents the geologic entity located by the mapped feature.

A mapped SHALL have a property that categorizes the sampling frame within which the mapped trace is located by the feature. Discussion: This enables mapping from a single coordinate pair (when the sampling feature is a 3-D line) or planar 2-D point, line or polygon (when the sampling feature is a surface) to a true 3-D trace.

A mapped feature instance is the result of one or more observations, and as such SHALL have an observation method property that categorizes the method used to characterize the feature properties; at least one value for the observationMethod property SHALL be specified; the ObservationMethod property shall be specified by a Category value.
Requirements to associate a DisplacementValue with a GeologicEvent entity that specifies the geologic age of the displacement event.
Requirements to describe a Displacement deformation, typically associated with a ShearDisplacement structure.
Sets out requirements to describe a displacement history for a geologic structure as a collection of DisplacementEvents bound to the structure by GeologicHistory relationships.
Base requirements class for geologicl structure elements

A DefiningStructureis a kind of GeologicFeatureRelation and SHALL inherit all the properties and requirements of GeologicFeatureRelation The 'source' of a DefiningStructure SHALL be a GeologicUnit entity instance for which the 'geologicUnitType' is "DeformationUnit" The 'target' of a DefiningStructure SHALL be a GeologicStructure entity instance
Requirements to associate a DisplacementValue with a GeologicEvent entity that specifies the geologic age of the displacement event.

A DisplacementEvent is a kind of GeologicEvent and SHALL inherit all the properties and requirements of GeologicEvent.
Informative: 'eventProcess' and 'eventEnvironment' value domains may be restricted to those values appropriate to displacement-type deformation.
Sets out requirements to describe a displacement history for a geologic structure as a collection of DisplacementEvents bound to the structure by GeologicHistory relationships.
Requirements to describe a Displacement deformation, typically associated with a ShearDisplacement structure.

A DisplacementValue SHALL have exactly one 'hangingWallDirection' property that is specified by a LinearOrientation entity A DisplacementValue SHALL have exactly one 'movementSense' property that is specified by a Term entity. A DisplacmentValue SHALL have exactly one 'movementType' property that is specified by a Term entity.
Informative: the 'hangingWalldirection', 'movementSense', and 'movementType' properties are voidable and are estimated properties.

A ShearDisplacementStructure is a kind of GeologicStructure and SHALL inherit all properties and requirements of GeologicStructure. A ShearDisplacementStructure SHALL have a 'faultType' property that is specified by a Term value. A ShearDisplacementStructure SHALL have a 'deformationStyle' property specified by a Term value.

A ShearDisplacementStructure SHALL have a 'totalDisplacement' property that is specified by exactly one DisplacementValue entity instance.
Informative: the 'totalDisplacement' property is voidable.

A ShearDisplacementStructure SHALL have a 'planeOrientation' property specified by a PlanarOrientation value
Informative the 'planeOrientation' property is voidable, and is an estimatedProperty.

A ShearDisplacementStructure SHALL have at least one 'physicalProperty' property specified by a PhysicalDescription entity instance.
Informative: the 'physicalProperty' property is voidable.

A FaultSystem is a kind of ShearDisplacementStructure and SHALL inherit all the properties and requirements of ShearDisplacementStructure. A FaultSystem SHALL have at least one 'faultSystemMember' that is specified by a ShearDisplacementStructure entity instance. A ShearDisplacementStructure SHALL have a 'system' property that is specified by a FaultSystem entity instance.
Informative The 'faultSystemMember' and 'system' properties are voidable.
IF the 'contactType' is "chronostratigraphicBoundary', a Contact SHALL have a 'correlatesWith' association with a GeochronologicBoundary Informative: The 'correlatesWith' property is voidable.

A Contact SHALL have one or more 'contactCharacter' property values that are specified by a Category entity. A Contact SHALL have one or more 'orientation' property values that area specified by a PlanarOrientation entity
Informative: The 'contactCharacter' and 'orientation' properties area voidable and are estimated propertues.

A GeologicContact is a kind of GeologicStructure and SHALL inherit the properties and requirements of GeologicStructure. A GeologicContact SHALL have a contactType property that is specified by a Term value
Base requirements class for geologicl structure elements
GeologicStructure element is abstract A GeologicStructure is a kind of GeologicFeature and SHALL inherit the properties, associations, and requirements of GeologicFeature.

A BoundaryRelationship is a kind of GeologicFeatureRelation and SHALL inherit all the properties and requirements of GeologicFeatureRelation The 'source' of a boundaryRelationship SHALL be a Contact entity instance. The 'target' of a BoundaryRelationship SHALL be a GeologicUnit entity instance
A GeochronologicBoundary is a kind of TimeOrdinalEraBoundary, and SHALL inherit all the properties, associations, and requirements of TimeOrdinalEraBoundary.

A GeochronologicBoundary SHALL have a 'stratotype' property that is specified by a StratigirpahicPoint entity instance.
Informative: the 'stratotype' property is voidable

A 'stratotype' property SHALL associate a StratigraphicPoint entity with a GeochronologicBoundary entity.
Informative: The 'stratotype' properties is voidable.

A GeochronologicEra SHALL have a 'start' property that is specified by either a NumericEraBoundary entity or a GeochronologicBoundary entity. A GeochronologicEra SHALL have an 'end' property that is specified by either a NumericEraBoundary entity or a GeochronologicBoundary entity. Informative: The 'start' and 'end' properties are voidable.

A GeochronologicEra SHALL have a related next era that is specified by the 'nextEra' property of the boundary that is the value of the 'end' property from the GeochronologicEra. A GeochronologicEra SHALL have a related previous era that is specified by the 'previousEra' property of the boundary that is the value of the 'start' property from the GeochronologicEra. Informative: The 'start', 'end' and 'stratotype' properties are voidable. The 'nextEra' and 'previousEra' properties are also voidable.
A GeochronologicEra SHALL be a component of a TimeScale.
A GeochronologicEra SHALL have an associated Term entity

A GeochronologicEra SHALL have a 'rank' property specified by a Term entity from a GeochronologicEraRank vocabulary. A GeochronologicEra MAY have associated 'member' GeochronologicEra entities. If a GeochronologicEra is the target of a 'member' association, the time interval it represents SHALL be a proper subset of the time interval represented by the GeochronologicEra that is the source of the association. The 'rank' property Terms SHALL have a defined partial ordering relation. If a GeochronologicEra is the target of a 'member' association, its rank property value SHALL be of lower rank than the rank assigned to the GeochronologicEra that is the source of the association.
GeochronologicEra is a subtype of TimeOrdinalEra and SHALL inherit all properties and relations from that class

A GeologicTimeOrdinalEraBoundary is a kind of TimeOrdinalEraBoundary and SHALL inherit all the properties and requirements from TimeOrdinalEraBoundary. The 'nextEra' and 'previousEra' properties from a GeologicTimeOrdinalEraBoundary SHALL have target values specified by a GeochronologicEra entity. An Instance of a GeologicTimeOrdinalEraBoundary SHALL be either a NumericEraBoundary, a StandardGlobalNumericAge, or a GeochronologicBoundary.

A GeologicTimescale SHALL have two or more 'referencePoint' properties specified by a TimeOrdinalEraBoundary entity that is either a NumericEraBoundary or a GeochronologicBoundary. The TimeOrdinalEraBoundary instances that are referencePoints in a GeologicTimeScale SHALL also be the boundary instances that fill the 'start' and 'end' property roles for the GeochronologicEras that fill the 'component' property roles for the GeologicTimeScale.

A GlobalStratotypeSection is a kind of StratigraphicSection and SHALL inherit all the properties and requirements of StratigraphicSection. Informative: A GlobalStratotypeSection represents stratigraphic section that has been adopted as a globally agreed standard to correspond to a period of geologic time.
A GeologicTimeScale SHALL have one or more 'component' properties that are specified by a GeochronologicEra entity
A NumericEraBoundary is a TimeOrdinalEraBoundary and SHALL inherit all the properties and requirements from TimeOrdinalEraBoundary.

A 'prototype' property SHALL associate one GeologicEvent entity to a StratigraphicPoint entity. The source GeologicEvent SHALL have an 'eventProcess' property that is a kind of stratigraphic process.
Informative: The 'prototype' property is voidable.
A StratigraphicSection is a kind of SF_SamplingCurve entity and SHALL inherit all the properties and requirements of SF_SamplingCurve.

A 'stratotype' property SHALL associated a StratigraphicSection entity with a GeochronologicEra entity.
Informative: The 'stratotype' properties is voidable.

A StratigraphicSection entity SHALL have the following properties: One 'geologicSetting' specified by a string value One 'geologicDescription' specified by a string value; One 'accessibility' specified by a string value; One 'conservation' specified by a string value. Informative: The 'geologicSetting', 'geologicDescription', 'accessibility', and 'conservation' properties of StratigraphicSection are voidable.
Requirements class that associates alteration description, Metamorphic description and bedding description with a geologic unit

A GeologicUnit is a kind of GeologicFeature and SHALL inherit all properties and requirements of GeologicFeature. A GeologicUnit SHALL have a 'geologicUnitType' property that is specified by a Term value. This property categorizes the geologic unit type with implications for some other property and relationship cardinalities.
A CompositionPart entity SHALL have a 'role' property specified by a Term entity.

A CompositionPart entity SHALL have a 'material' property that is specified by a CompoundMaterial entity.
Informative: The 'material' property is an estimated property.
Requirements class that associates alteration description, Metamorphic description and bedding description with a geologic unit

A BeddingDescription SHALL have at least one 'beddingPattern' property that is specified by a Category entity. A BeddingDescription SHALL have at least one 'beddingStyle' property that is specified by a Category entity. A BeddingDescription SHALL have at least one 'beddingThickness' property that is specified by a Quantity entity.
Informative: The 'beddingPattern', 'beddingStyle', and 'beddingThickness' properties are voidable and are estimated properties.
A GeologicUnit SHALL have a'bedding' property that is specified by a BeddingDescription entity. Informative: The 'bedding' property is voidable.
A GeologicUnit SHALL have at least one 'alterationCharacter' property that is specified by an AlterationDescription entity. Informative: alterationCharacter is a voidable property.

A GeologicUnit SHALL have at least one 'metamorphicCharacter' property that is specified by a MetamorphicDescription entity.
Informative: metamorphicCharacter is a voidable property.

A GeologicUnit entity SHALL have a 'geochemistry' property specified by a ChemicalComposition entity
Informative: The 'geochemistry' property is voidable.

A GeologicUnit entity SHALL have at least one 'physicalProperty' property specified by a PhysicalDescription entity
Informative: The 'physicalProperty' property is voidable.
